  "text": "RT variants affecting fidelity mapped to three regions: the fingers region, the p51 subunit β7/β8 loop, and the αA helix. Fingers region variants (V60A, A62T, I63K and F77S) probably alter nucleotide binding and specificity. The p51 subunit variants might exert a long-range effect on nucleotide discrimination at the active site, as Nissley et al. [CITATION_1] and Ambrose et al. [CITATION_2] demonstrated with RT mutation I132M, which confers hypersensitivity to NRTIs. Variants in the αA helix (C38S, E42K) could modify the interaction between RT and the template nucleic acid feeding into the active site. Biochemical and retrotransposition assays showed that several fidelity variants misincorporated nucleotides and that some might compromise viral replication.",
